## Requirements (verbatim)

> # Reconfigure Extension UI for Improved Navigation
>
> ## Problem
> The current extension UI is cluttered with a large number of buttons, resulting in a disorganized experience that is difficult to navigate and visually overwhelming.
>
> ## Requirement
> Transition the interface to a cleaner layout that supports specific task types and reduces visual noise. Users need to categorize refinements (Task vs. Engineering Handoff) and select complexity levels (Extended vs. Basic).
>
> ## Proposed Solution
> - **Dropdown Menus:** Replace high-volume buttons with a dropdown to select refinement types and tiers.
> - **UI Scaling:** Reduce the size of remaining functional buttons.
> - **Iconography:** Integrate icons for secondary actions like copying to save space.
> - **Settings Migration:** Move secondary tools, such as the latest debug log, into a dedicated settings menu to declutter the primary view.
>
> **Estimation:** 5 Sprint Points.

> # Unify Prompting Logic and Interface Architecture
>
> ### Problem
> The current system separates "short" and "extended" prompting workflows into distinct markdown-based logic. The extended workflow creates a chain of independent refinements, while the short workflow is a single-step process. This redundancy makes managing prompt behavior difficult and creates unnecessary friction when switching between modes.
>
> ### Requirement
> - Create a unified prompt structure that supports both short and extended workflows using the same interface.
> - Implement a "Chain of Events" structure where independent sections can be toggled.
> - Introduce a toggle/checkbox for "Extended" mode to dynamically inject additional personalities and processing steps into the prompt chain.
> - Dynamically manage API calls based on the active workflow behavior.
> - Explore transitioning the extension interface to a more fluid HTML-based page to support complex menus and API interactions while keeping the core extension lightweight.
>
> ### Solution
> - Refactor the prompt builder to treat "Short" and "Extended" as configuration options within a singular architecture rather than separate code paths.
> - Develop a modular UI layout that permits independent section configuration.
> - Evaluate moving interface logic to a dedicated HTML/JavaScript view to improve user control and extensibility.
>
> **Estimation:** 13 Sprint Points.

