## Current state

- Popup exposes 4 mode buttons (`exact`, `ai-refine`, `extended-refine`, `extended-handoff`) + stop / copy-latest / copy-debug-log + settings.
- Two backend paths: `runStandardRefinementJob` (1 call) and `runExtendedRefinement` (~17 calls, persona chain). `EXTENDED_PIPELINES.refinement` / `.handoff` already configure extended type as data.
- Short path uses the single active prompt; it has no Task/Handoff concept yet.
- Transcript ingestion is centralized in one `resolveTranscript` seam (both paths). A `Manual transcript` textarea + `Use pasted transcript as the only source` toggle give three modes: **off** (Otter only), **supplement** (Otter + appended paste, default when text present), **override** (paste replaces Otter, skip injection + tab requirement). Per-use only â€” never persisted, resets off on popup open. Direction / direction-override / extended chain apply unchanged.
- Otter-transcript validation is stricter: `content.js` `extractTranscriptText()` returns `{ text, method, lineCount }`; `assertUsableOtterTranscript` (both paths) rejects empty / `method:"none"` / low-confidence `container` fallback below 400 chars / below `MIN_TRANSCRIPT_CHARACTER_COUNT` (100). The standard path previously had no floor. Supplement mode errors out rather than falling back to manual-only.
- Refine inputs are **failure-recoverable**: the popup snapshots all inputs (manual transcript + toggle, direction + override, Type, Extended) to `chrome.storage.local` (`ottercopy:ui:lastAttempt`) on run-start, keyed to the runId. On reopen, `restoreLastAttemptIfNeeded()` restores them iff that run `failed`/`cancelled` (shows the error, ready to retry with a different model/API); a `completed` run clears the snapshot. Happy path still opens fresh (only `UI_PREFS_KEY` promptId/extended restore).

