### 2026-07-01T16:29:05Z â€” OtterCopy â€” Failure-aware input persistence (retry after failed/cancelled runs)

**Summary.** User QoL follow-up: refine inputs were always cleared on popup reopen (happy-path assumption). If a run **fails** (e.g. API/model unavailable) the user lost everything and had to re-enter it. Now a failed **or** cancelled run preserves its full input set so the reopened popup reconstructs the attempt, shows the error, and the user retries â€” typically after switching model/API. Only a successful run clears.

**Mechanism (popup-only; background untouched â€” it already records terminal status + error).**
- New device-local key `ottercopy:ui:lastAttempt` (`chrome.storage.local`; may hold a large transcript, so local not sync). Shape `{ runId, inputs: { promptId, extended, direction, directionAsPrompt, manualTranscript, manualAsOnlySource } }`.
- `saveLastAttemptSnapshot(runId)` â€” written in `copyFromActiveTab` after each refine start returns `{ ok, runId }` (all three refine modes; not the plain `exact` copy). Overwrites any prior snapshot (fresh attempt).
- `restoreLastAttemptIfNeeded()` â€” on open, reads the snapshot + latest result (`getLatestRefinementResult`). If `runId` matches and status is `failed`/`cancelled`, restores all six fields, calls `updateExtendedGating()`, and surfaces the error via `setStatus(..., "error")`; keeps the snapshot. If `completed` / no result / runId mismatch, clears it. `running` â†’ left untouched.
- Init reordered: `initializeSettings().then(async () => { if (!(await restoreLastAttemptIfNeeded())) loadUiPrefs(); })` â€” a restored failure sets promptId/extended itself, so generic prefs apply only on the happy path.
- `announceLatestResultTransition` clears the snapshot when a run completes while the popup stays open.
- Promisified `chrome.storage.local` get/set/remove helpers so init can await them.

**Files/areas.** `popup.js` â€” `LAST_ATTEMPT_KEY`, storage helpers, `saveLastAttemptSnapshot`/`clearLastAttemptSnapshot`/`restoreLastAttemptIfNeeded`, snapshot writes on both refine start branches, init reorder, clear-on-completed.

**User-visible impact.** A failed/stopped refine no longer wipes the user's work â€” reopen shows the same transcript/direction/Type/Extended plus the failure reason, ready to change model and re-run. Successful runs behave as before (fresh popup).

**Decision.** Revises the earlier "no persistence" stance: persistence is now scoped to failure recovery only (device-local, cleared on success). The manual-transcript-in-storage tradeoff is accepted solely for this recovery snapshot, per user request.

